collections.name: Guillotine Process
collections.description:
The philosophy of the Process is a great combination of contradictions that, when united, achieve balance. The pursuit of freedom through questioning the established order; the symbolism and veneration of divine figures; along with the consolidation of power to govern oneself, is what unites such opposing individuals. But since one must see to believe, the great Molotov forged a tool that embodies it all: the Guillotine. A symbol of power, justice, and revolution.
Justice or damm Process!

collections.name: Lisy | First Paintings Collection
collections.description:
Welcome to First Paintings, an intimate NFT collection featuring the earliest works created by Lisy across three homegrown studios in Brooklyn, New York; Cleveland, Ohio; and San Antonio, Texas. These paintings carry the fingerprints of beginnings—raw, searching, intuitive.

The journey starts in Greenpoint, Brooklyn. My studio was a sun-drenched room in an apartment, perched on the west-facing side of the building. With bay windows framing the Manhattan skyline, I painted under the gaze of the Chrysler Building and the United Nations. That room doubled as both studio and living room all in one. Blessed with a laid-back landlord who didn’t mind oil paints in the apartment (thank you, universe), I leaned fully into my process—experimenting, remembering, and discovering.

This collection is more than just “firsts.” It’s a map of becoming. A digital archive. A love letter to the magical beginnings of an artist claiming space.

collections.name: Galaxy by Lion K. J.
collections.description: The artist behind this painting, owned by HoraSpatium, is Lion K. J., an emerging painter who transitioned from a distinguished career as an executive at Samsung Electronics, where he played a pivotal role in the strategic planning of Galaxy smartphones. Drawing profound inspiration from the vastness of space and celestial phenomena, he pioneered a unique brushstroke technique that masterfully evokes the grandeur of galaxies on canvas. Upon close examination, each meticulously placed dot appears as a distant star, radiating light toward the observer, encapsulating the multidimensional essence of the cosmos. This particular piece belongs to his renowned Galaxy Series and is rendered on a canvas measuring 72.7 x 60.6 cm. The exclusive intellectual property rights to this painting are held solely by HoraSpatium.
